channel.title: Silabsoft client v4.0?!?! :confused:
channel.description:
ppl think they know it all.. but i do everything everyone has told me to do, still doesnt work, ive downloaded the winRar client or what ever, i have the most updated software for every gaming need on my computer, i have the newest java, which is 6.3 to let u know. and ive downloaded silabsoft client v4.0, but every time i download, extract with winRaR, it brings up the same god damn window its as follows
*****Sorry, an error has occur whilst loading RuneScape
To fix this try the following (in order):
1: Try closing ALL open web-browser windows, and reloading 2: Try Clearing your web-browsers cache from tools->internet options 3: Try using a different game-world 4:Try rebooting your computer 5:Try selecting a different version of Java from the play-game menu****** also saying!*****java.io.FileNotFoundException: c:windows\mpr_file_store_32\silabdat_0.idk <The System cannot find the file specified>
now if done ALL of those, cept #5, i dont have a play-game menu, that message shows up like almost immediatly as i try to access the update server part of the loading bar, now i also have no clue how to downgrade my Java. soo plz ppl! help me!!! :confused: :confused:
